Usage:
	cyarg --lib <dir>
	Launch a Yarg REPL, using <dir> as the root of the Yarg library.

	cyarg --lib <dir> <path> [-- [args]]
	Run a Yarg script at <path>, using <dir> as the root of the Yarg library.
		Optional [args] following -- are available to the script in hostArgs.

	cyarg --help
	Display this help message.

	cyarg --bootstrap <path>
	Execute a Yarg script, without the language context. For testing of cyarg.

	cyarg --compile <path>
	Compile a Yarg script, reporting any compilation errors.

	cyarg --disassemble <path>
	Disassemble a Yarg script, displaying the generated bytecode.
